                  <h2>NEVER OVER FLAVOR YOUR RECIPE!</h2>
                  <p>Here’s how you can avoid over flavoring your recipes. If you’re flavoring cookies or ice cream, start with a small amount such as a .25% up to 1% of total weight of the batch. Then, taste the flavor in the finished dough or ice cream mix. If you enjoy the flavor and it disappears after 3-5 seconds then it’s perfect. However prior to baking, we suggest adding 10% more flavor oil to compensate for the loss of flavor during baking. When making and freezing ice cream, it is also possible the oil will become diluted due to the whipping of air into the product from the ice cream machine. So, you may need to add more flavor oil to the ice cream mix.</p>
               </div>
            </div>
